==English==

===Etymology===
Hebrew יִשְׁמָעֵאל (Ishmail), meaning: "God hears or obeys". Standard Yišmaʿel, Tiberian Yišmāʿêl; Arabic: إسماعيل, Ismā'īl).

===Proper noun===
'''Ishmael'''

# (''Bible, Old Testament'') the eldest [[son]] of [[Abraham]] and his wife's handmaiden [[Hagar]] who were cast out after the [[birth]] of [[Isaac]]; [[traditionally]] the [[ancestor]] of the [[Arab]]s.
#{{given name|male|}} A male [[given name]].

